<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, saying he will make make the trade bill an
issue in his campaign against George Bush: ``I think the issues of
workers being laid off, what is happening to the industrial base of
this country, and the failure of this administration to do much to
deal with that ... will be very much one of the major issues.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, contradicting statements by his campaign manager
that he is no longer seeking to win the Democratic nomination after
a series of losses to Dukakis: ``We're winning every day on this
long and tortuous journey to the White House. ... Nothing and
nobody is going to turn us around.''
   
   ANDREW YOUNG, mayor of Atlanta, on Jackson's candidacy: ``It
really doesn't help at all if he's not elected president. It's not
just a matter of feeling good. Jesse ran to see some good done for
poor people and black people.''
   
   JOHN SASSO, Dukakis' former campaign manager who left his job
after embarrassing the candidate last year, on his current
relationship with Dukakis: ``Mike and I are good friends, and, as
he has said, we still talk from time to time, discuss things. But I
have no active role with the campaign.''
