<HEAD>Fire Breaks Out In Psychiatric Wing Of London Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Firefighters rescued six psychiatric patients and
evacuated 200 others after fire broke out in a west London
hospital, staff members said.
   The six rescued patients were treated for smoke inhalation
Thursday night in the emergency center of Ealing Hospital and were
in satisfactory condition. No other injuries were reported.
   Dr. Raphael Eban, unit general manager of the hospital's general
wing, said the fire caused substantial damage to a section of the
psychiatric ward.
   Police and fire officials were investigating the cause, Eban
said.
   ``Some of the patients were so confused they wanted to carry on
watching television in smoke-filled rooms,'' said John Norris,
divisional officer of the London Fire Brigade.
