<1ST_LINE>r a PM-DoctorCharged     04-29 0189</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Doctor Charged,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gynecologist Charged With Sexual Battery For Performing Abortion
on Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gynecologist was charged with
sexual battery after he allegedly handcuffed his wife and performed
an abortion on her, authorities said.
   The 52-year-old doctor, who operates a clinic where abortions
are performed, was arrested Wednesday. Prosecutors said he could
face more charges.
   ``If in fact this occurred, and this person is a physician, it's
beyond comprehension,'' Broward County Judge J. Bart Budetti said
Thursday in setting bond at $50,000. The doctor, who refused to
speak during the hearing, posted the bail.
   The 37-year-old woman was treated and released at Broward
General Medical Center, where a doctor confirmed that she'd had an
abortion, police said.
   The gynecologist allegedly handcuffed his wife Sunday as she was
lying in bed, took her into the bathroom and performed an abortion
on her 11-week-old fetus without anesthesia because she refused his
sexual advances, said police spokesman Ott Cefkin.
   The doctor told her as he performed the abortion that if she
didn't stay still, he would inject her with something to calm her
down, police said.
</TEXT>
