<HEAD>Ferry Tips Over, No Immediate Reports of Serious Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BREMERHAVEN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A car ferry crashed into a dock
and tipped over, tossing 21 crewmen into the water, police said.
Authorities said no serious injuries were reported but further
investigations were under way.
   In a brief statement issued to the news media, Bremerhaven
police said the accident occurred when the 607-foot ferry hit the
Seebeck dock in this northwestern port city.
   All 21 crewmen were plucked out of the water and were being
checked for possible injuries, the statement added.
   The statement provided no details about whether any passengers
were on board, or where the vessel was coming from when the
accident occurred.
   A Bremerhaven police official, speaking to The Associated Press
on the condition of anonymity, said that circumstances surrounding
the accident were still incomplete and that an investigation was
under way.
   Rescue crews in boats and helicopters quickly converged on the
scene after the accident.
