<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Iran-Drugs,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iran Reports More Than 10 Drug Smugglers Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iranian Revolutionary Guards killed more
than 10 heavily armed drug smugglers in the eastern province of
Kerman, Tehran radio reported Thursday.
   It quoted authorities as saying the guards ambushed a group of
smugglers stationed in the mountains southeast of the city of
Kerman, the provincial capital.
   During the fighting, the report said, more than 10 of the
smugglers were killed. The radio did not give an exact date for the
incident.
   According to the report, the smugglers carried anti-aircraft
weapons, offensive missiles, radios and other weapons, and killed a
number of Revolutionary Guards in the skirmishes.
   The report did not say what type of drugs were being smuggled,
but Iranian media have recently reported the arrests of a number of
heroin dealers. The drugs were smuggled across Iran's eastern
border with Afghanistan or Pakistan.
