   Actor Martin Sheen has agreed to produce TV
movies for the new Turner Network Television, the Turner
Broadcasting System announced Friday.
   TBS said it reached an agreement with ITC Production and
Symphony Pictures Television, the production company founded by
Sheen and partner William Greenblatt.
   The first project to be produced under the agreement will be
``The Last Missile,'' to star Sheen and actor-singer Kris
Kristofferson.
   TNT is a new cable entertainment channel being developed by TBS,
which owns Atlanta-based WTBS-TV and Cable News Network.
