<HEAD>Ambassador Urges Europe to Do More for Western Security</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Ambassador Richard Burt urged the
NATO allies Friday to do more for Western defense.
   ``Europeans must do more for and among themselves to contribute
to their own defense, in Europe and beyond,'' he told an American
Chamber of Commerce meeting in Hamburg.
   ``Europe's stake in the international arena is often equal to or
greater than that of the United States, for example in questions of
access to raw materials such as oil and international markets.''
   U.S. legislators have spoken in recent months of a growing
belief among Americans that Europeans do not contribute enough
toward Western defense.
   Rupert Scholz, who takes over as West German defense minister
next month, was quoted by the newspaper Die Welt as saying in an
interview: ``It is not a matter of money alone. It is ability and
performance as well.''
   He said West German and U.S. defense interests cannot not be
separated.
</TEXT>
