<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Cameroon-Election,0089</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>President Biya Re-elected</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YAOUNDE, Cameroon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Paul Biya was re-elected to a
second five-year term, the Supreme Court announced Friday.
   Biya, the sole presidential candidate, got 98.75 of the 3.32
million votes cast Sunday. More than 93 percent of Cameroon's 3.6
million registered voters participated in the presidential and
legislative elections.
   Voters in many districts were allowed to choose between two
candidates for the 180-seat National Assembly but all candidates
were chosen by the Democratic People's Assembly, the only legal
political party.
