<HEAD>Car Ferry Crashes Into Dock; Crewmen Rescued</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BREMERHAVEN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A car ferry undergoing repairs
hit a dock Friday and tipped over, temporarily trapping 21 crewmen
and workers, but no injuries were reported, police said.
   Port authority officials said the cause of the accident was
being investigated.
   Harbor police said the accident occurred at 3:15 p.m. when the
600-foot ferry crashed into the Seebeck dock in this northwestern
port.
   Police spokesman Peter Gusovius said all 21 crewmen and workers
aboard were rescued by helicopters and boats.
   ``They were all taken from the ferry,'' he said. ``No one was in
the water.''
   Gusovius said the ferry Kattegat is registered in the
Philippines and was in Bremerhaven for repairs. Crews were working
Friday evening to right the vessel, he said.
