<HEAD>Four Countries Removed From Preferential Tariff Treatment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan said he removed four
countries from the list of those receiving preferential tariff
treatment under the Generalized System of Preferences for
developing nations.
   Reagan's action affects articles imported from Bahrain, Bermuda,
Brunei Darussalam and Nauru.
   He said he had determined that the per capita gross national
product of those countries for fiscal year 1985 exceeded the limit
provided in the law that set up the system of preferences in 1974.
