<TEXT>
   Bank of New York Co. says nearly half of Irving
Bank Corp.'s outstanding shares have been tendered under its $1
billion-plus hostile buyout offer, giving it an apparent edge in
its battle to acquire Irving.
   But Irving's ``white knight'' merger partner, Banco Commerciale
Italiana SpA, said Thursday it remained committed to buying a large
stake in Irving as part of a major restructuring plan Irving
